com.fortify.processrunner.processor

Class AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapFromGroupedObjects

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fortify.processrunner.processor.AbstractProcessor
      • com.fortify.processrunner.processor.AbstractProcessorGroupByExpressions
        • com.fortify.processrunner.processor.AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapFromGroupedObjects
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICLIOptionDefinitionProvider, IProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTargetProcessor, SSCTargetProcessorSubmitIssues

    public abstract class AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapFromGroupedObjects
extends AbstractProcessorGroupByExpressions

    This abstract class allows for building an object map from grouped objects. Objects are grouped by our parent AbstractProcessorGroupByExpressions class. In our processGroup(Context, String, List) method we build an object map for the current group, and then call processMap(Context, String, List, LinkedHashMap) to allow concrete implementation to further process the object map.

    The Map will initially be built based on the first object in the group and the configured key/expression pairs configured via setFields(LinkedHashMap). Then, for every object in the group, values for fields configured through setAppendedFields(LinkedHashMap) will be appended to existing map values.

    Author:
    Ruud Senden
